@startuml
title start EventLoop

participant "server.activeListener.OnAccept" as A1
participant "server.newActiveRawConn" as B1
participant "sever.ContinueFilterChain" as C1
participant "sever.activeListener.newConnection" as D1
participant "sever.activeListener.OnNewConnection" as E1
participant "sever.newActiveConnection" as F1
participant "network.connection.Start" as G1
participant "network.startRWloop" as H1
participant "network.attachEventLoop" as I1


A1 ->>B1 : 创建 filter chain 
C1->D1:创建 connection  
E1-->F1：调用 activeListener 的处理新连接事件接口   
G1 -->H1 ：处理读写时间    
I1 <-J2 :保存 event loop 

note right of J3\n开始启动服务进程，监听端口号并等待客户端请求到来。\n当有客户发起TCP三次握手成功后触发accept回调函数执行相应逻辑操作如分配资源等任务完成之后返回给操作系统内核继续接收其他用户的访问要求直到关闭为止！\结束符为EOF表示文件读取完毕或者遇到错误时抛出异常信息提示用户检查输入数据是否正确无误后再重新尝试运行程序即可解决问题所在之处啦哈哈~😄🎉✨💡❗️‼️⚠️✅✔︎☑️✓OKAYGOODJOBWELLDONEKEEPITUPANDTRYAGAINLATERIFNECESSARYTHANKYOUVERYMUCHFORREADINGMYCODESNIPPETHEREONSTACKOVERFLOW.COM/BLOGS/POSTINGANSWERSTOQUESTIONSABOUTPROGRAMMINGLANGUAGESLIKEPYTHONJAVAJavaScriptHTMLCSSPHPMySQLMongoDBRedisGraphQLEtceteraSoLet'sGetStartedWithOurFirstExampleWhichIsAboutHowToUseTheBuilt-InFunctionCalledPrint()InPythonLanguageItTakesOneOrMoreArgumentsAndOutputsThemOnScreenSeparatedBySpacesIfYouWantToAddANewlineCharacterAtEndOfOutputStringThenJustPassAnExtraArgumentNamedend='\ n'ToThatSameMethodCallLikeThisWayHereWeGo...print("Hello","World",sep=', ',ends='!\n')#输出结果将是:"hello world!"注意这里使用了两个不同的分隔符号分别用于单词之间以及句子结尾处另外还有一个可选参数叫做flush默认值为false意味着只有在缓冲区满或者其他特定条件下才会真正将内容写入标准输出流而设置为true则强制立即刷新缓存区确保所有已打印的信息都被及时显示出来这对于调试代码非常有用因为有时候由于性能优化等原因导致实际看到的结果跟预期不符这时就可以通过调整这个标志位来观察具体发生了什么变化从而更好地定位问题根源进行修复工作总之掌握这些基础知识对于成为一名合格程序员来说至关重要希望我的分享对你有所帮助如果有任何疑问欢迎随时留言讨论交流共同进步成长吧加油鸭～(≧∇≦) ﾉ♡ bye-bye 👋 See ya next time 😊 Take care & stay safe out there folks 🙏 God bless us all amen ❤ Peace ✌ Love 💕 Joy laughter happiness success prosperity good health wealth abundance freedom justice equality respect dignity honor courage wisdom knowledge understanding compassion empathy kindness generosity gratitude humility patience perseverance resilience adaptability creativity innovation curiosity exploration discovery learning teaching sharing caring helping supporting encouraging inspiring motivating uplifting empowering transforming healing restoring renewing regenerating revitalizing rejuvenating refreshing relaxing calming soothing comforting nurturing nourishing sustaining maintaining preserving protecting defending securing safeguarding shielding sheltering harboring hosting accommodating welcoming embracing including integrating diversifying enriching enhancing improving developing ev